<title>USA: AGCO to buy German firm, plans shr offering.</title>
<headline>AGCO to buy German firm, plans shr offering.</headline>
<dateline>ATLANTA 1997-01-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>AGCO Corp said it has entered an agreement to buy private German tractor company Xaver Fendt GmbH &amp; Co for $283 million, plus $38 million in debt.</p>
<p>The agricultural equipment firm also said it plans to soon file a registration statement with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission for the sale of 4.5 million common shares to help finance the transaction.</p>
<p>The company said it expects to receive approval for the transaction by the Federal Cartel Office in Germany by the end of the month.</p>
<p>AGCO said the acquisition will make it the market leader in Germany and give it the second market share position in France.</p>
<p>((New York Newsdesk, 212/859-1700))</p>
